---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BrandMark from '../components/BrandMark.astro';
import ReadingLayout from '../components/ReadingLayout.vue';
import { loadStats } from '../lib/stats';
import { formatBytes, formatNumber } from '../lib/ssr';

const stats = loadStats();
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Essenfont"
  description="Essenfont is a universal Unicode 17 font — one redistributable OpenType file covering every assigned codepoint, assembled from OFL-licensed donor fonts."
  canonical="/about"
>
  <ReadingLayout client:visible>
    <article class="about container" data-reading-article>
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1>One font, every codepoint</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Essenfont</strong> is a real font — not a library or a service. A single
        redistributable OpenType Collection (OTC) that covers every assigned Unicode 17
        codepoint ({formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} characters across
        {stats.unicode.blockCount} blocks), built from {stats.donorCount} canonical
        OFL-licensed donor fonts.
      </p>
      <p>
        There is no UFO source, no hand-designed glyphs. Every glyph is vector-extracted
        from canonical donor fonts — Noto, Full-Sung, UniHieroglyphica, and more. The
        build is purely an assembly pipeline: read donors → partition by plane → stitch
        into subfonts → pack into a collection.
      </p>

      <h2>The name</h2>
      <p>
        <em>Essen</em> — German for "to eat" — because a universal font is meant to be
        consumed everywhere. The "font" is the object. Together: a font that eats every
        script.
      </p>

      <h2 id="logo">The mark</h2>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Logo philosophy ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="logo-philosophy">
      <div class="logo-gallery logo-gallery--two">
        <figure class="logo-figure logo-figure--light">
          <img src="/essenfont-logo_light.svg" alt="Essenfont mark in light mode (blue)" width="192" height="192" />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="logo-fig-label">Light · Blue</span>
            <span class="logo-fig-caption">illumination — the calm authority of a clear sky, the colour of daylight on paper.</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="logo-figure logo-figure--dark">
          <img src="/essenfont-logo_dark.svg" alt="Essenfont mark in dark mode (red)" width="192" height="192" />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="logo-fig-label">Dark · Red</span>
            <span class="logo-fig-caption">rubrication — the medieval practice of marking important initials in vermilion, lit by the lamp that keeps the page readable at night.</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="prose logo-prose">
        <p>
          The Essenfont mark is shaped as the hexagram <strong>Gen</strong> (<span class="glyph-big">☶</span>), the fifty-second hexagram of the I&nbsp;Ching. <em>Gen</em> means <em>mountain</em> — stillness, the root from which all creation grows. The mountain does not move; everything else moves around it. So too does a universal typeface anchor every script in Unicode while remaining itself unchanged.
        </p>

        <h3>The empty that provides utility</h3>
        <p>
          Look at the negative space inside the hexagram's lines: it forms the letter <strong>E</strong>. This is no accident. Laozi wrote in the <em>Dao De Jing</em>:
        </p>
        <blockquote class="dao-quote">
          <p>
            Thirty spokes share one hub —<br/>
            it is the emptiness at the center that makes the wheel useful.<br/>
            Shape clay into a vessel —<br/>
            it is the void inside that holds what you pour.<br/>
            Cut doors and windows for a room —<br/>
            it is the gap that lets the light in.
          </p>
          <cite>— Dao De Jing, ch. 11</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          The logo's translucent, glass-like quality embodies this principle.
          Essenfont is transparent: it claims no authorship of its glyphs, takes no
          credit for its donor outlines, and hides nothing about its build pipeline.
          Its usefulness comes from what it <em>contains</em>, not from what it <em>is</em> — the empty vessel that holds every script.
        </p>

        <h3>Two colors, one motion</h3>
        <p>
          The logo exists in two color variants — <span class="color-chip color-chip--blue"></span> blue (illumination, the calm authority of a clear sky) and <span class="color-chip color-chip--red"></span> red (rubrication, the medieval practice of marking important initials in vermilion). Together they represent motion: the mark shifts from blue to red when you interact with it, just as a universal font shifts between scripts without losing its identity. The duality echoes the <em>yin</em> and <em>yang</em> — two forces, one mark.
        </p>

        <h3>In darkness, clarity</h3>
        <p>
          In dark mode, the mark sheds its background entirely. The mountain stands alone,
          struck by no surrounding frame. As the Heart Sutra teaches:
        </p>
        <blockquote class="dao-quote">
          <p>
            Form is emptiness, emptiness is form.<br/>
            In darkness, you distinguish both dark and bright more clearly.
          </p>
          <cite>— Prajñāpāramitā Hṛdaya Sūtra</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          The dark variant is the more striking of the two — not because it adds, but
          because it subtracts. The background falls away, and the mark's essential
          geometry — the mountain, the E, the emptiness at the center — becomes
          unmistakable. What remains when everything unnecessary is removed is what
          was always there.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>The technical achievement</h2>
      <p>
        The canonical output is <code>Essenfont-Regular.otc</code> ({formatBytes(stats.fontBinaries.otcSizeBytes ?? 0)}), an OpenType Collection with CFF2 outlines and CBDT color emoji bitmaps, partitioned across the five planes that carry assigned Unicode 17 characters. The website serves {stats.websiteSubsets.woff2Count} per-block WOFF2 subsets ({formatBytes(stats.websiteSubsets.woff2TotalBytes)} total) so visitors don't download the full {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)}-codepoint font just to browse one script.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every WOFF2 subset loads in Chrome's OpenType Sanitizer — a goal that required
        13 named fixes across three repos. See the <a href="/docs">engineering story</a> for the full account.
      </p>

      <h2>License</h2>
      <p>
        Essenfont is a <strong>mixed-license</strong> font. Most donors are
        OFL/Apache/MIT/BSD licensed, but some (notably FSung / Full-Sung) impose
        additional restrictions (non-commercial use). The assembled font inherits
        the most restrictive term across its donors. Each donor's license terms are preserved in the font's <code>name</code> table and in the auto-generated <code>LICENSE-SOURCES.md</code>. See the <a href="/license">license page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Get it</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/download">Download from GitHub Releases</a>, install via <a href="https://github.com/fontist/fontist">Fontist</a>, or read the <a href="/docs/usage">How to use</a> guide to pick the right format for your use case:
      </p>
      <pre><code>fontist install "Essenfont"</code></pre>
    </section>
  </article>
  </ReadingLayout>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
  .page-head { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .logo-prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ef-accent);
  }
  /* ─── Logo philosophy section ──────────────────────────── */
  .logo-philosophy {
    margin: 3rem 0;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
  }
  .logo-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    align-items: end;
  }
  .logo-gallery--two {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .logo-figure {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--ef-rule-strong, rgba(26,24,21,0.16));
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .logo-figure--light {
    background: var(--ef-bg, #faf8f5);
    border-color: rgba(42, 92, 138, 0.25);
  }
  .logo-figure--dark {
    background: #161513;
    border-color: rgba(176, 64, 64, 0.45);
  }
  .logo-figure--dark .logo-fig-label,
  .logo-figure--dark .logo-fig-caption { color: #ecdfd0 !important; }
  .logo-fig-label {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ef-text-2);
  }
  .logo-figure img {
    width: 144px;
    height: 144px;
    object-fit: contain;
  }
  .logo-figure figcaption {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-text-3, #8a8478);
  }
  .logo-figure .mono {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ef-text);
  }
  .logo-fig-caption {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-body);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    color: var(--ef-text-2);
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 26ch;
  }
  .logo-prose {
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .glyph-big {
    font-size: 1.75em;
    line-height: 0;
    vertical-align: -0.1em;
    color: var(--ef-accent);
  }
  .dao-quote {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.75rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ef-accent);
    background: var(--ef-surface, #f2efe9);
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .dao-quote p { margin: 0; }
  .dao-quote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-text-3, #8a8478);
  }
  .color-chip {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 0.75em;
    height: 0.75em;
    border-radius: 50%;
    vertical-align: -0.05em;
    margin-right: 0.15em;
  }
  .color-chip--blue { background: #1a3a8a; }
  .color-chip--red  { background: #9b2d2d; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .logo-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
    .logo-gallery--two {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .logo-figure img { width: 128px; height: 128px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .logo-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
